as for numbers best numbers i ever made were on a soul binder where 75 attack increased damage 25%.  but i honestly didnt think that was a good test.  its a high mitigation mob where i was using a change from 1075 to 1150. pretty low attack against that kind of AC.  when in game i feel the effect most every point after 1275 against those mobs.  and it showed weirdness in the parse. when i looked at the numbers for a 20 minute run at soul binder the backstab didnt change with attack.  which is just wrong.  one of the reasons i key off 1300 attack is cause thats where i start to see back to back max backstabs.  a clear and solid change.  but to see no change at all in the backstab against the soul binder shows me that something was missing in my test.   <br>
<br>
one thing bout damage gains via increase in attack is that they stack well with haste.   heres what i mean if you manipulate the equations a fbss comes out to a 121/100 = 21 % increase in damage over time.  but with a 60% haste it becomes 181/160 a 13% increase in damage with an fbss over without.  still not bad.  but that effect isnt in attack gains.  its an increase of damage per an average hit.  the faster you chop the better the results.<br>
<br>
and lastly nobody gets to say str is unimportant without saying primal is useless.   there is someone out there choking over the idea that avatar is a crap buff.  an increase in attack is an increase in attack.<br>
