<br>
For AC, there is a believed &quot;soft cap&quot; at around 1250 for velious mobs, mainly because the atk of the velious ubermobs are around a certain number (not sure exactly how they relate to each other).  The soft cap in kunark was around 1150-1200 I think, 1100 for old world.  This is all because the atk/lvls of mobs were getting higher.  After this the returns for raising your AC drastically decrease.. which is why so many warriors look for hp gear over high ac gear after they get 1200-1250 unbuffed.<br>
<br>
The same would go for ATK, I would think.  After you get it to extreme lvls, getting it higher wont do all that much.  So while going from 1200 to 1270 may have a big effect, going from 1400 to 1470 may not, both depending on the mob.  High ATK wont have as much of an effect on lower level, older world mobs than it will on higher end things. And of course, Colach is right about the raw atk vs str atk... its the same thing with AC - AC from armor mostly adds to the &quot;mitigation&quot; part of your AC, while skills (and agi, to a very small degree) and buffed AC add to &quot;avoidance&quot; AC (I think on the buffed part). <br>
<br>
I havnt really researched ATK and such, since I play a Warrior as a melee, so I might be totally wrong ;O <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=5794">Bippity</a> Hierophant / <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27969">Gobbo</a> Warlord
